{
  "texts": [
    "The adaptive learning rate is calculated for each parameter wi using the square root of the previous gradient exponential average, as in Formula 32.",
    "Adam (Adaptive Moment Estimation) was introduced by Kingma and Ba in 2014 as an alternative to determining the learning rate.",
    "Adam's method combines the momentum and RMSProp methods to calculate model parameter changes [262].",
    "First, Adam calculates the momentum mt based on the gt gradient using Formula 34.m t = β 1 m t-1 + (1 -β 1)g t(34)Then calculate RMSProp vt based on the squared gradient g 2 t using the Formula 35.v t = β 2 v t-1 + (1 -β 2)g2 t (35) Stat., Optim.",
    "12, July 2024 WARTO ET."
  ]
}